<C>__{heath}
<D>__{so these power cuts will continue unless we can reach a compromise.}
<A>__{edward heath is in mid flow.}
<C>__{heath }
<D>__{the miners are asking for a 35% increase in wages. obviously we can't go anywhere near that. the unions are not our enemies and never have been. we want and have always wanted the broadest consensus...}
<A>__{the ministers nod. margaret determinedly edges a little forward so that she is in equal line with the other male}
<B>__{ministers.}
<C>__{heath }
<D>__{i'm sure we are all in agreement that we must do nothing for the moment that will further inflame the current situation.}
<C>__{minister 1}
<D>__{hear hear, prime minister.}
<A>__{margaret leans forward for a better view, trying to catch his eye. heath wavers, mid speech. all turn to look at margaret who sits unwavering. heath resumes.}
<C>__{heath}
<D>__{ the fact of the matter is, it's absolutely crucial that we are seen by the public to be acting as conciliators and not aggressors.}
